                    },
                    "body": "The fix for this issue broke controller naming, or perhaps it slipped through.\n\nPlease see:\nhttp:\/\/www.nabble.com\/Controller-Naming--tf2847594s16154.html\n\nWas not sure if this should reopen or if a new bug should be filed.  But either way, here it is ;)\n\nThanks,\nRalph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-04T10:51:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-04T10:51:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12098",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Matthew,\n  If you want to chat about this issue, please let me know, I think I have some thoughts concerning your intentions when this fix was made, and what its trying to accomplish, find me on AIM or Email,\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-04T10:57:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-04T10:57:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12109",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ralph -- let's connect on IM -- I'm curious what changed with the controller naming. With the current revisions, it does what was orginally intended, plus allows underscores so that you can use subdirectories ('\/admin_login' maps to 'Admin_LoginController', which looks in 'Admin\/LoginController.php', for instance). Send me an email with your IM details (matthew@zend.com is my email).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-05T11:54:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-05T11:54:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12268",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Resolved in revision 2840. Both word and path separators may now be configured via accessors in the dispatcher. By default, '-' and '.' act as word separators, and '_' acts as a path separator. Dispatcher logic has been revamped and simplified to allow this.\n\nModules simply concatenate the module name with the controller name using an underscore, allowing directory segregation of controller classes.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-16T21:36:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-16T21:36:30.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
